==Old English==
===Etymology===
From West Germanic: cognate with Old Frisian [[dern]], Old Saxon [[derni]], Old High German [[tarni]].

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /'dyrne/

===Adjective===
'''dyrne'''
# [[secret]], [[hidden]]
#:''Ne sceal dyrne sum wesan'': nothing must be secret.  (''Beowulf'')

